<title>USA: Intelligent Electronics settles litigation.</title>
<headline>Intelligent Electronics settles litigation.</headline>
<dateline>EXTON, Pa. 1997-02-20</dateline>
<text>
<p>Intelligent Electronics Inc said Thursday it agreed to pay $10 million to settle class action litigation brought against it, certain of its present and former officers and directors, and its auditors.</p>
<p>It said the settlement, over which it reached an agreement in principle with the plaintiffs, will be funded by $3.8 million of corporate funds and the balance by insurance.</p>
<p>The settlement is subject to court approval, it said.  </p>
<p>The company said that the litigation was pending in the U.S. District Court for the Eastern District of Pennsylvania and the Philadelphia Court of Common Pleas.</p>
<p>Intelligent Electronics is an information technology products and services provider.</p>
